The Nigeria Union of Local Government Employees (NULGE) has commenced an enlightenment campaign to mobilize support for the Kaduna State government measures to curb the spread of Coronavirus  in the state. The state president of the union, Comrade Rayanu Isyaku Turunku, who disclosed this in Kaduna, said the decision is to educate the rural populace on the dangers of the disease and its consequential effect if people ignore the government measures, especially the restriction order. He said that while some people still argue that the coronavirus is not real, others believe that  the restriction order is harsh and an imposition of unnecessary hardship on the people. Comrade Rayanu stressed that the safety of lives is paramount and praised the state governor, Mallam Nasiru Ahmed el-Rufai, for his firm decision to do the right thing and the needful to prevent the spread of the disease. He prayed for the quick recovery of the Governor to enable him return to office to continue with his good work, while also commending the state deputy governor, Hajiya Hadiza Balarabe, for her diligence. Rayanu  appreciated the state government decision  to roll out palliative measures,  which include distribution of food items to the households, especially the most vulnerables to cushion the effects of the restriction order but however,  urged the  government to ensure transparency in carrying out the  programme to achieve the impact and the desired objectives. NULGE also appealed to public spirited individuals and organisations to support the government by providing assistance to families in the rural areas who are more affected by the stay at home order as many families have been cut off from their source of daily livelihoods.  